The song "I Will Always Love You" was written by American singer-songwriter Dolly Parton. She originally wrote and recorded the song in 1974 as a country ballad. The song became a major hit for Parton, but it gained even greater popularity when it was covered by Whitney Houston for the soundtrack of the 1992 film "The Bodyguard." Houston's version of the song became one of the best-selling singles of all time, winning numerous awards and topping the charts in multiple countries. Despite the success of Houston's version, the song remains a beloved classic and a signature song for Parton.